Reminder: Fall Sports Picture Day is Wednesday, August 12th starting at 9:30!! Here is a reminder from Keepsake:

**************************
With sports pictures coming up, we wanted to make sure you noted a change.

Keepsake Portraits will be using a new way of ordering sports pictures. Your student will bring home a card that explains how to get online, see your images, and order. Everyone will be photographed.

You may also select direct to home shipping if you would like! That way you won’t have lost pictures in duffel bags. You may go to www.KeepsakeClients.com to print and send a paper form, but we think you will like the new system better.

Do not hesitate to text/call Keepsake at 419-422-4121.

Again, you won’t preorder sports this year like the past with an envelope, so your student won’t be bringing one home.

*************************

post_text: Newest construction on our school prairie site included drilling holes for our fencing and bird perching posts. Thank you to Kenny Palte, and Brad Brooks who donated their machines, tools, time, ideas and energy to make this happen. Thanks also to Kahle-Verhoff for support in our efforts to obtain the materials for this phase of the prairie installation. Two-rail vinyl fencing will be installed in the coming week. Grant sponsors which funded our prairie include Corteva, Bayer, USFWS, Monarch Joint Adventure, Pollinator Project, TransCanada, Pheasants Forever, Quail Forever.

For families wishing to get physicals now, you can do so. You will need to go the the OHSAA website and print the form from there. Here are your steps to accomplish this:
1.) Open up OHSAA.org
2.) Click on the Sports Medicine tab
3.) Click open the Pre-Participation Physical Form option, and then print off the 20-21 form.
4.) When you finish, you can bring them up to the school or have your student-athlete give it to their coach to turn in to
the office.
5.) Please update Final Forms when that is ready for the 2020-2021 school year

post_text: Construction has begun on our prairie. You will see evidence of this as you drive into the school on the north side of the road. There will also be a raptor perch, songbird perch and learning knoll (great idea Ben) that will serve as an outdoor learning area for our students within the prairie.Thank you to Joe Niese who prepped materials and Ben Hopps who led the crew. Thanks also to Emma and Jackson Martini, wildlife biologist for Pheasants Forever and Quail Forever, for being on hand to set posts and measure out the site. It will be a work in progress for several months. You won't see flowers until next summer but it will be worth the wait. Thank you Nick Langhals, president of our local Black Swamp Pheasants Forever and Quail Forever for helping with the grant process. Thank you to the additional sponsors for the grant which funded our prairie including Corteva, Bayer, USFWS, Monarch Joint Adventure, Pollinator Project, TransCanada, Pheasants Forever, Quail Forever.

post_text:
Miller City - New Cleveland Local School District is seeking qualified applicants for a Special Education Aide / Classroom Aide for the 2020/2021 school year.

Miller City-New Cleveland Local School is a rural school in Putnam County, Ohio with a Grades K-12 enrollment of approximately 470 students. The district has consistently ranked in the top 5% of Ohio public schools in terms of the performance index measure attached to state standardized testing. The Miller City and New Cleveland communities value education and take pride in the programs of the school system.

Candidates are asked to submit the following to Mr. Dustin Pester, Elementary Principal: A letter of application emphasizing qualifications and reasons for interest, an up-to-date resume, and professional references. Please email this information to pester_d@mcncschools.org .

Deadline for application is Wednesday, June 17.

Listen—there’s a better way! Join Mark Myers in Financial Peace University classes, and we’ll learn how to beat debt and make a plan for the future . . . together! Interested? Miller City - New Cleveland School was planning on hosting Financial Peace University on site, but because of COVID-19 the course will be offered virtually.

If you are looking to learn how to pay off debt fast, save and spend wisely, and build wealth this is a course for you! Planning for the future is hard when you’re still paying for the past! Listen—there’s a better way! Join Mark Myers in Financial Peace University classes, and we’ll learn how to beat debt and make a plan for the future . . . together! Interested? Join virtually starting Wednesday, June 10, 2020. Feel free to message Mark (through the link below) your questions or sign up at
https://www.financialpeace.com/classes/1116203?c=ccf&fbclid=IwAR1Ze7eeHVkrwdaFdL9J5kj-Xt8kTLSKRsWmVMu8ljEtmuplJhF4-Vqr1kE

post_text:
Attention all 2020-2021 7th-12th graders that are considering playing athletics during the coming school year:

With the COVID-19 shut down of our school building, we are not able to provide physicals this year, so please plan accordingly. If you will be participating in a fall sport, you will need your physical and all other forms filled out by August 1st, 2020.

All forms including the physical form need to be approved at the next school board meeting, June 8th 2020. The new forms for the upcoming school year will not be available until July 1st. We ask you to be patient with the new Final Forms system and wait to get your physicals after that date.

Thank you for your patience, and looking forward to seeing you all next fall!!!

It is here!! The Miller City Athletic Department Laundry Detergent/Body Wash Spring Fund-raiser.

You should be getting contacted by the same athlete that sold to you last year to see what you would like. Nothing has changed in the quality and products that we are offering.

If you are not contacted by somebody, you can e-mail your order to mcad@mcncschools.org. Deadline to order will be Sunday, April 19th.

You can pay for your order when you come to pick it up at the front of school. Please make any checks out to Miller City High School.

Delivery date will be Saturday, May 2nd from 9am-11am. You will drive in the front entrance and we will place your order in your vehicle.

If you have any questions just e-mail us at mcad@mcncschools.org and we will help you with answering them. Thank you so much for your support of Miller City Athletics!!!

Julia's artwork will be displayed at Rhodes State Office Tower, in Columbus, Ohio from February 22nd to March 18th, 2020. Congratulations Julia

post_text:
First grader, Kendall S., was chosen as an exhibitor for the 40th Annual Youth Art Month Exhibition sponsored by the Ohio Art Education Association.

Her artwork will be displayed in the Youth Art Month Exhibition at the State Teacher’s Retirement Systems (STRS) building, in Columbus, Ohio. The artwork will be on display from February 22nd to March 21st, 2020 during normal business hours from 9:00 AM to 4:00 PM, Monday through Friday.

There are eight regions in Ohio representing the OAEA, this year’s show includes one hundred thirty-eight student artworks from all over the state. It is a distinct honor for any student to have artwork in this exhibition, congratulations Kendall!

Miller City-New Cleveland Cafeteria is looking to add more people to our sub list. The person applying would need to be available for an early morning call, for a sick employee or a call ahead for a scheduled appointment or time off.

Job Description: Work from 7:30-1:00 Cooking, Serving, & Cleaning up. Running a commercial dishwasher, some heavy lifting is required. These people would also be trained into upcoming contracted positions as they become available. For more information contact Diana Kuhlman Cafeteria Manager at kuhlman_d@mcncschools.org or call the school.

post_text: Congratulations to MCHS Agribusiness instructor Mr. John Koenig for being recognized as one of ten finalists for Ohio's Golden Owl Award. Sponsored by Nationwide, Ohio FFA and the Ohio Farm Bureau, the Golden Owl Award recognizes agricultural educators across Ohio for their tremendous contributions to helping the next generation of agricultural leaders. For his efforts, Mr. Koenig was recognized at a student assembly on January 15 where he received a commemorative plaque and $500 award. As a finalist, Mr. Koenig is now in the running for the honor of 2019-20 Ohio Ag Educator of the Year which will be announced in April. Good luck, Mr. Koenig!

post_text: Thank you, MCVFD for bringing Santa to our school today!
shared_text:
Miller City VFD is with Erica Verhoff.
December 20, 2019 at 1:15 PM ·

It’s the most magical time of year, and we all loved seeing the smiling kids faces this morning at school!! Santa told us after we left that, he always enjoys visiting the kids at school because everyone is so friendly and polite with “Please” and “Thank You” for everything!! The fire department loves keeping this tradition alive and seeing all the joy and happiness it brings to everyone throughout the entire school is what makes it all worth it!! We hope everyone has a very blessed and safe Holiday Season!! Merry Christmas!!! 🎄 🎅🏼 🎁

post_text: The 2021 junior English class opened the ten-year-old time capsule today (that was made by the class of 2011 when they were juniors). Mr. Heuerman, a teacher at MC, was a member of the class of 2011 and was able to read his letter that he and his friends wrote to the juniors when they were 1st graders. Inside the letter, they discussed what life was like in 2010 in connection with family life, religion, school, violence, lifestyles, and government. They then predicted what life would be like today. Surprisingly, they were correct in that all hs students would have iPads with their books on it. At the time they wrote the letter, there was a total of 10 iPads in the school.

"❤️ " them!

Pre-sale tickets for the Division IV Volleyball Regional Semi-Finals game this Thursday, October 31st have finally arrived!! Tickets are one price only - $6 per ticket. At the door all tickets will be $8. Our school will receive a portion of the pre-sale, so buy your ticket early! You can purchase the tickets during school hours on Mon 10/28, Tues 10/29 and Wed 10/30 ; 8-2:30. On Thursday, 10/31, you can purchase them until 11:30am.

There will be a $2 charge for parking at The Elida Fieldhouse

Signs, school banners, balloons, pennants, shakers, debris such as confetti, noisemakers such as sirens, horns, bells, drums, etc are NOT premitted!! The Elida schools prohibits body or face paint in the Fieldhouse.

Come on out and cheer our Regional Qualifiers on as they play to move on:)

post_text:
Presented by Nationwide, the Ohio FFA and the Ohio Farm Bureau, the Golden Owl Award recognizes agricultural educators across Ohio for their tremendous contributions to helping the next generation of agricultural leaders. Students, fellow teachers and other supporters can nominate their favorite agricultural teacher and summarize what makes him or her the best in the state.

Nominees have an opportunity to win great cash prizes and the distinction of being Ohio’s Agricultural Educator of the Year. Prizes include:

$500 and an engraved plaque for each of the 10 honorees
$3,000 for the Golden Owl Award winner (Ohio Agricultural Educator of the Year).
To nominate someone for the Golden Owl Award visit pages-nationwide.com/OWL_2019/. This year’s nominations must be submitted by Nov. 16, 2019.
